Create: 
	- .github/copilot-instructions.md
		Always-on or pattern-based	
		Team standards and default behaviour
		e.g. Use Python for backend services and React for frontend components.
	- .github/prompts/*.prompt.md
		Manual, on-demand slash command	
		Repeatable one-shot tasks
		e.g. /release-notes that always follows a fixed changelog format, pulling context from recent commits.
		You find yourself typing the same complex requests into Copilot Chat repeatedly. "Generate unit tests following our pattern with mocks..." and you have to explain the pattern every single time.
	-. github/agents/*.agent.md
		Selected agent mode/persona	
		Specialised role plus tool control
		do not use for general coding help or tiny tweaks
	- .github/skills/<name>/SKILL.md
		On-demand and auto-discovered	
		Reusable multi-step workflows with resources
		do not use for simple standards or hard policy enforcement
		You need AI agents (not just chat) to understand specialized tasks in your domain. When Coding Agent or other AI agents work on your repository, they should automatically know how to perform QA-specific operations.
	- .vscode/mcp.json or user mcp.json
		Tool and data connectivity	
		Live access to external systems and APIs

