copilot-instructions:
- Framework-wide coding standards
- Architecture patterns everyone should follow
- Technology stack preferences
- Security requirements

Prompt files:
- Repetitive tasks with specific patterns
- Documentation generation
- Code review checklists
- Test generation workflows

Skills:
- Teaching AI agents domain-specific tasks
- Multi-step workflows with validation
- Tasks requiring specific tools or commands
- Procedures that benefit from working examples


Agent:
- Implementing defined issues from backlog
- Adding test coverage
- Refactoring existing code
- Updating documentation
- Fixing bugs with clear reproduction steps

Agents use:
Custom Instructions: Coding Agent reads these to understand your coding standards
Agent Skills: Coding Agent loads relevant skills to perform specialized tasks
Prompt Files: You don’t directly use these with Coding Agent (they’re for you in Chat)


Start Here: What are you trying to accomplish?
1. "I want ALL code suggestions to follow our framework patterns" → Custom Instructions (.github/copilot-instructions.md)

2. "I keep asking Copilot Chat to do the same task repeatedly" → Prompt File (.github/prompts/task-name.prompt.md)

3. "I want AI agents to know how to perform a specialized QA task" → Agent Skill (.github/skills/skill-name/SKILL.md)

4. "I have a complete task that needs implementation" → Coding Agent (assign GitHub issue to @copilot)
